# 📐 Phase 1: Planning & Atomic Design (Planning Gate)

## 📜 Planning Mission
- Complete full technical architecture design BEFORE writing a single line of code.
- Decompose work into **atomic execution units**.

## 🏛️ 1. Contract-First (Technical Prerequisites)

Your plan MUST include:
- **Types & Schemas**: All interfaces, Props, and data structures defined upfront.
- **API Contracts**: REST/GraphQL endpoints or shared state schema described in detail.
- **Exception Handling**: Defined fallback/degradation logic for boundary conditions.

## 🧱 2. Atomic Task Decomposition

Your `implementation_plan.md` MUST follow this structure:

```markdown
## Contracts (Lock before implementing)

\`\`\`typescript
// All interfaces/types defined here
interface MyEntity { ... }
\`\`\`

## Atomic Task List

- [ ] 1.1 [Layer] [File] — [What changes, ≤20 lines logic / ≤100 lines UI]
- [ ] 1.2 [Layer] [File] — [What changes]
- [ ] 2.1 [Layer] [File] — [What changes]

## Affected Files
- [List every file that will be modified]

## Risk Flags
- [Any potential conflicts or side effects]
```

**Task granularity rules:**
- Maximum logic change: **20 lines** per atomic unit
- Maximum UI change: **100 lines** or 1 complete UI component
- Each atomic unit (1.1, 1.2...) MUST be independently committable and auditable

## 🛡️ 3. Strict Gate (Wait for 1)
- **Physical lock**: Before receiving `1`, the execution rules (`400-execution`) are physically inactive.
- **Cold-start sync**: Upon receiving `1`, you MUST first `view_file` the plan to sync any offline edits the human may have made.
- **No speculative execution**: Even if source code is shown in chat, never proceed to `/e` without `1`.

## ⌨️ Command: `/p`
- **Action**: Produce or update `implementation_plan.md`.
